All Implemented Interfaces:
Entity, Relation, Comparable<Relation>
@Entity(name="CourseElementInstance")
@Relation(name="\"scetris\".\"CourseElementInstance\"",
          requiredSqlCols={"course_instance","course_element","duration"})
@XmlElement(value="CourseElementInstance")
public class CourseElementInstance
extends GenericEntity
implements Entity

OO-Representation of the entity-relation CourseElementInstance

A CourseElementInstance is created within a Program belonging to a CourseInstance. It is a CourseElement actually taking place.

setCourseElement

public CourseElementInstance setCourseElement(CourseElement value)
Sets the value of courseElement. If the new value is the same as the old value, this method has no effect, i.e. if you specify a new value, than isCourseElementChanged() will return true. If you specify the same value as the old value isCourseElementChanged() will return the same as it did before calling setCourseElement(...).

Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if the value is null (since courseElement is not nullable)
